===Etymology===
Greek πλαγκτoν (''wanderer'' or ''drifter'').

===Mass noun===
#a generic term for all the [[microorganism]]s that float in the [[sea]]. 
===Derived terms===
*'''[[Phytoplankton]]''': small [[algae]] and [[fungi]]. They obtain energy by [[photosynthesis]], and live mostly in the upper part of the sea, because they need [[light]] to survive.
*'''[[Zooplankton]]''': small [[protozoa]], [[crustacean]]s (such as [[krill]]), etc. and the [[egg]]s and [[larvae]] from larger animals. 
